# Python pipeline

- Target Python 3.12 with practical type hints and Pydantic boundary validation.
- Keep coordinate conversion in `coordinates.py`; Unreal Y negation belongs there only.
- Cache public downloads and make network tests opt-in.
- Preserve malformed feature details in rejection reports.
- Avoid unstructured dictionaries in business logic after ingestion.
- Keep generated output deterministic; use stable hashes, not process-random values.
- Run `ruff format`, `ruff check`, and `pytest` from `tools/geo_pipeline`.
